cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with understanding semantic similarity among images. It may also belong to Multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with learning human perceptions of images. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses collecting and embedding qualitative measures. Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) are also possible sub-categories as the paper involves optimization algorithms and clustering queries.
